  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Manager",
  "description": "<p>1.      Project Planning &\nCoordination</p><ul><li>Develop project schedules, milestones, and resource allocation plans.</li><li>Coordinate with consultants, subcontractors, suppliers, and internal teams.</li><li>Ensure timely submission of shop drawings, method statements, and material approvals.</li></ul><p>2.      Execution & Supervision</p><ul><li>Oversee site activities for ACMV installation, testing, and commissioning.</li><li>Monitor progress against schedule and resolve technical/site issues promptly.</li><li>Ensure compliance with safety regulations, quality standards, and environmental\nrequirements.</li></ul><p>3.      Budget & Cost Control</p><ul><li>Prepare and monitor project budgets, cost forecasts, and cash flow.</li><li>Review and approve variation orders, claims, and progress payments.</li><li>Optimize resource utilization to achieve cost efficiency.</li></ul><p>4.      Regulatory & Compliance</p><ul><li>Ensure adherence to Singapore Building and Construction Authority (BCA), Workplace\nSafety and Health (WSH), and relevant statutory requirements.</li><li>Liaise with authorities for inspections, permits, and approvals.</li></ul><p>5.      Team Leadership & Communication</p><ul><li>Lead and motivate project engineers, supervisors, and site staff.</li><li>Conduct regular project meetings with stakeholders.</li><li>Provide clear reporting to senior management on project status, risks, and\ndeliverables.</li></ul><p>6.      Quality Assurance</p><ul><li>Implement and enforce quality control procedures.</li><li>Ensure proper documentation of testing, commissioning, and handover processes.</li><li>Address defects and warranty issues within stipulated timelines.</li></ul>",
